                    <div class="navItems">
                        <a class="navItems-home" href="http://localhost:8000/">Home</a>
                        <a class="navItems-contact" href="http://localhost:8000/contact">Contact</a>
                        <a class="navItems-about" href="http://localhost:8000/about">About</a>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </div>
    <div class="mainC">
        A URL shortener is a tool that converts a long URL into a much shorter, more manageable version. These shorter
        URLs redirect users to the original, long URL. The main purposes of using a URL shortener include:
        <br><br>
        <ul>
            <li>Ease of Sharing: Short URLs are easier to share on social media, emails, and other platforms where space is
                limited or a long URL might look unwieldy.
            </li>
            <li>
                Tracking and Analytics: Many URL shorteners provide detailed analytics, such as the number of clicks, geographic
                location of the clicks, and the referring sites.
            </li>
            <li>
                Customization: Some services allow you to create custom short URLs that are easy to remember or brand-specific.
                Cleaner Appearance: Shortened URLs look cleaner and more professional, which can be particularly beneficial in
                marketing and promotional materials.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        
        
        Popular URL shortening services include Bitly, TinyURL, and Google's URL shortener (though it has been
        discontinued). Users typically paste their long URL into the shortener tool, which then generates a shorter
        version to use as needed.
    </div>
